<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Avocado Moulded Salad</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Salads &amp; dr</cat>
        <cat>To post</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>package</unit></amt>
        <item>Lime Gelatin Powder</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Warm Water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>can</unit></amt>
        <item>(1 Lb.) Crushed Pineapple; drain-reserve liquid</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>tablespoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Lemon Juice</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Mayonnaise</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3/4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Whipped Cream</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Avocado (Ripe &amp; Soft); diced</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Dissolve jello in water and stir in 1/2 cup pineapple juice. Cool. When it
  thickens, add pineapple. Salt and add lemon juice. Fold in mayonnaise,
  whipped cream and avocado. Mould.
  
  Source: Recipes Out of This World Women of St. Agnes Catholic Church
  Charleston, WV 1969
  
